description: Deletes an Amazon FSx backup. After deletion, the backup no longer exists, and its data is gone. The DeleteBackup call returns instantly. The backup won't show up in later DescribeBackups calls.

parameters.name: BackupId
parameters.description: The ID of the backup that you want to delete.

parameters.name: ClientRequestToken
parameters.description: A string of up to 63 ASCII characters that Amazon FSx uses to ensure idempotent deletion. This parameter is automatically filled on your behalf when using the CLI or SDK. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: BackupId
nested_items.description: The ID of the backup that was deleted.

nested_items.name: Lifecycle
nested_items.description: The lifecycle status of the backup. If the DeleteBackup operation is successful, the status is DELETED.
